🧱 B01 — BLOCK 2 of 8 — Create three local option sets (Choices)
Important terminology check first. Modern Power Platform calls these Choices (singular per column, with "Choices" as the entity type). Old terminology = "Option Sets" / "Local Option Set" / "Global Option Set". Same thing.
There are two scoping flavors:

Global Choices (created at solution level, reusable across tables)
Local Choices (embedded in a single column, not reusable)

For B01/B02 we want GLOBAL Choices, because pei_ruleoutput will be reused on the pei_ruleversion Output Snapshot column in B02. Creating them global once means a single source of truth for the binary Applicable/Not Applicable verdict across both tables. (The other two — pei_rulecollectionscope and pei_rulestatus — could be local since they're only used on pei_rule, but creating them global keeps the pattern consistent and costs nothing.)
Where to create them in the maker portal:
Solutions → Evidence Management System (your solution, visible in the breadcrumb in Image 2) → + New → More → Choice.
Create each in turn. After the third, return here.

